## Vercel Web Analytics Installation

Successfully installed and configured Vercel Web Analytics for this React + Vite project.

### Changes Made

**1. Installed Package:**
- Added `@vercel/analytics` (v2.0.1) to package.json dependencies
- Updated package-lock.json with all necessary dependencies

**2. Modified Files:**
- `src/App.jsx`:
  - Imported `Analytics` component from `@vercel/analytics/react`
  - Added `<Analytics />` component to the main App component
  - Wrapped the existing `<Routes>` with a React fragment (`<>...</>`) to accommodate the Analytics component

### Implementation Details

Following the official Vercel documentation for React/Vite projects:
- The Analytics component is placed at the app's root level in the main App component
- This ensures analytics tracking is active across all routes and pages
- The component automatically handles page view tracking and web vitals collection

### Testing & Verification

✅ Build completed successfully with no errors
✅ Linter passed with no new warnings or errors (only pre-existing warnings remain)
✅ All existing functionality preserved
✅ Lock file updated to ensure consistent dependency resolution

### Next Steps

To enable analytics in production:
1. Deploy the application to Vercel
2. Navigate to your project's Analytics tab in the Vercel dashboard
3. Click "Enable" to activate Web Analytics
4. Analytics will begin tracking page views and web vitals automatically

### Technical Notes

- Framework: React 19.2.6 with Vite 8.0.12
- Package Manager: npm
- Analytics Package Version: @vercel/analytics@2.0.1
- Implementation follows official Vercel quickstart guide for React/Vite applications
